name: Dale Wimer
description: I started my real estate career in 2003 at small independent firm, and in 2008 I received my broker's license. In 2011 I joined Prudential Ambassador Real Estate which is now Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate. I have a lovely wife and 2 great kids that I just can't get enough of!  I am part of the Elite Nebraska Real Estate Team. Since 2014 the team has been in the top 10 for sold homes in the entire Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices nationwide franchise (over 55,000 agents strong). The team set a state record for home sales in 2019 with 550 home sales for the year!

name: Katie Adams
job_title: VP Corporate Relocation Services  and Business Development

name: Chelsea Karlgaard
description: Times have changed in real estate and it's time to bring back the art of the deal while leveraging the latest technologies. My clients can expect that I deliver value in my data based market knowledge, organized systems that are designed to create a pleasant experience when buying or selling a property, and sharp negotiating skills that were honed by years of commodity purchasing.

name: Jace Thompson
description: Jace has a natural knack at helping his clients feel well cared for and understood. He takes great pride in helping them find the perfect home for their needs. A fully licensed agent, Jace hones his real estate skills by furthering his education at the University of Nebraska Omaha where he is majoring in Business Administration with concentrations in Real Estate and Land Use Economics. Originally from Tilden, Nebraska, Jace has traveled extensively across North America, soaking in the sites and appreciating new, local cultures. He relishes learning about new places and adapting to the new environments he experiences. When he’s not working, you might find Jace on a run, helping refresh and redesign a room.

name: Lyndsey Golden
description: As a real estate professional at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, I understand the importance of working with an agent who will have your best interests at heart. That is why I believe in customer service above all else and believing that every individual deserves my full commitment and loyalty.

name: Karen Jennings
description: As a passionate and persistent Realtor, I'm humbled and honored to provide quality leadership with the highest degree of integrity. Developing a solid, trustworthy relationship with my clients is the key. My experience includes Corporate and Military Relocation, Single Family Homes including Luxury Homes, New Construction, Acreages, Farms, and Commercial properties. I have been helping clients buy and sell real estate since 2002 and am licensed in both Nebraska and Iowa. I am a member of the National Association of Realtors, Omaha Area Board of Realtors, Great Plains Multiple Listing Service, Midlands Regional Commercial Information Exchange, and Nebraska Real Estate Association. As the leader of the JENNINGS TEAM, I look forward to serving you!

name: Leah Johnson
description: Hi! I'm Leah, a Council Bluffs native and licensed real estate agent in Iowa and Nebraska. I'm the Team Leader of Fairway Real Estate Group, a small real estate team at BHHS Ambassador Real Estate. My niches include helping first-time buyers navigate the home buying process and working with sellers to get top dollar for their homes. I'm also an investor-friendly agent!

name: Annali Leach
description: & The Will2Way® Promise!

name: Allen Osborn
description: Meet Allen Osborn! Allen was born and raised in western Nebraska, attended the University of Nebraska Kearney, and currently resides in Omaha. For the last decade, he has developed and prospered relationships through his teaching and coaching career. Allen has a passion for public service and strives to build strong relationships and connections through a person-served lens, which aligns with his real estate endeavors. With a background in sales and management, he prides himself on effective communication and having a strong work ethic. He acts with integrity to treat each person as family through their buying, selling, and investment goals.

name: Ann Townsend
description: As part of a relocated family, Ann has the first-hand experience with all the emotions, stress and logistics of moving a household, family and life to a new city. With a father who is a disabled veteran, transitioning military families in and out of our community is her sweet spot.

name: Shannon Sorensen
description: It’s no secret, there’s a lot of realtors in our metro area! I’ve had the privilege of working with many of them over the past 6 plus years. I hope to continue fostering those business relationships and build more connections with realtors and my clients.

name: Carla Vigness
description: I moved from MA to NE about 28 years ago and have been working in sales and marketing since. My goal is always to make my clients’ experience a positive one while making sure to have fun in the process. As your realtor, you will always be my top priority and I will be with you every step of the way during the entire buying or selling process.

name: Margaret VonTersch
description: You don’t need a real estate agent every day.

name: Shelli Novotny
description: I am a full time Realtor. I have an Associate Brokers License.

name: Kim Hoffart
description: Kim has been selling residential real estate for over 30 years. She was born and raised in Omaha, and graduated from Westside High School and The University of Nebraska - Lincoln with a major in Communications. Kim has been blessed over the years with many repeat clients and referrals. Finding just the right home for her clients is a top priority. She believes there is no better satisfaction than seeing a family's house become a home to them. Kim stays very involved in your own neighborhood chairing the activities committee and being a member of the HOA board. In her free time, she enjoys spending time with friends and family.

name: Mahlon Rador
description: Meet Mahlon Rador!  Hard work and dedication are in his DNA. From working on the farm to serving as a Haz-mat technician and being a family man, he prides himself on great communication, guidance, and integrity.  Born and raised in the Cornhusker state, he has experienced city and rural living, enjoying all the recreation this great state has to offer.  Mahlon has earned real-life experience in customer service, sales, marketing, and real estate investing.  With a genuine love for real estate, he is thrilled to represent buyers and sellers in achieving homeownership.

name: Steve Scherich
description: Finding your dream home shouldn't be like looking for a needle in a haystack, it just takes an agent with integrity and patience.

name: Nic Luhrs
description: Nic is a real estate and investment professional with a background in team management, business ownership, and valuation. Having owned and operated several businesses; including retails stores and property management. Nic brings a unique approach to best strategize your home selling and buying experience. He first found his interest in the world of real estate through investing in rental properties.  He treats every client as if it were family; keeping their best interests in mind.  He has now taken this interest along with his expertise to guide his clients through a seamless and stress free process. He develops strong, long lasting relationships with his clients.  Nic doesn’t work on transactions, he works on relationships and guarantees you will enjoy working with him. You will experience a greater sense of trust through the streamlined and thorough processes that Nic uses to oversee every step of your real estate endeavors.

name: Ben Proctor
description: I am happy to say that this is now 20 years in the real estate industry. I have been lucky to acquire expansive knowledge in several areas of residential real estate including relocation, development, sales, marketing, and management.

name: Kristina Oreskovich
description: Grounded by her Cornhusker roots, Kristina understands what makes Nebraska a special place to call home.  Her friendly and outgoing nature, coupled with exceptional communication skills, allows her to connect effortlessly with clients. As a devoted wife and mother of two wonderful kids, Kristina cherishes her connections with family and friends.

name: Lynn Smith
description: More information about me.

name: Ken Bartholomew
description: As a Realtor and local business owner, executive and entrepreneur, I bring a unique blend of expertise, a strategic mindset, and a comprehensive understanding in navigating complex negotiations and contracts, ensuring favorable outcomes for clients. I am passionate about helping individuals and families find their dream homes and make sound real estate investments.

name: Mallory Young
description: As a Nebraska native and a licensed real estate professional with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, I recognize and value the trust my clients place in me, and I strive every day to exceed their expectations. As a long time resident of the Omaha area I will lead you in the right direction while explaining every step of the way! I will keep my clients updated on market trends and keep an open line of communication day or night. My goal is to make your real estate dreams a reality!

name: Carmen Bunde
description: Full-Time REALTOR

name: Lyn Echter
description: Integrity. Service. Knowledge is what I feel are the most important attributes to being a successful real estate agent. I am a MULTI-MILLION TOP PRODUCER and have been selling real estate in Omaha and the surrounding area for many years.  Many years ago, I decided to become a Certified Home Stager. I thought having this certification would be a HUGE benefit to my sellers….and it truly has.  I have been STAGING all the homes I list for the past ten years…. and it works.  There is no cost for this service.  I have a warehouse full of furniture, accessories, pillows, artwork plus more!

name: Sheila Ost
description: Pursuing My Dream as a Real Estate Agent

name: Christie Oberto
description: “There’s no place more important than home.”

name: Monserrat Avalos Pantoja
description: I, Monserrat, am excited to help you, my client throughout your journey in finding your dream home! Waking up in an accommodating home and environment is the key to making memories, grow, and nurture together as a family. The journey there should not be a problem more nonetheless a stressing experience. My goal is to be with you along the way by offering my dedication, aspiration, and proficiency to your goal.

name: Townsend Lanphier Group
description: Whether you're working directly with Ann or Kathy, you'll always have access to both. That's because, while they each have different experiences and skillsets, they work together and share a common goal of making sure their clients have the best buying and selling experiences possible. Every time.

name: Christina Reinig
description: My name is Christina Reinig and I have a passion for helping people. My first vocation was as a teacher and then a gifted facilitator at Gretna High School for over 19 years. There I learned to engage the students and helped them achieve their goals and taught problem-solving techniques. As I transitioned into real estate, I found the same skills I learned as a teacher applies to real estate.

name: Macey Incontro
description: As a Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate agent, Macey prides herself on her ability to provide world class, personalized service to her clients. Understanding every home, every client, every need is unique; she represents every transaction with integrity, honesty, and empathy. To her, creating lifetime memories and making her clients feel like family is why she got into this business.

name: Brodie Wakefield
description: Providing help to others is Brodie’s top priority and has been for many years. Born and raised in Kennard, NE; Brodie found his passion for helping others by joining the Volunteer Fire Department. He is a graduate of the University of Nebraska at Omaha with a Bachelor’s degree in Emergency Management minoring in Business. Pursuing Real Estate has allowed him to use his expertise in management, communication, and familiarity with Omaha and the surrounding areas. Brodie will always go the extra mile to ensure his clients have a positive experience while buying, selling, or building a new home. He’s very passionate with what he does and wants nothing but success for his buyers and sellers!

name: Kristie Kuo
description: What Kristie loves:

name: Klaire Cross
description: Klaire is in her first year of real estate. She is also the executive assistant to team leader Gail Hunter. Klaire graduated from Lewis Central High School, after she completed a Bachelor's of Communication degree from Graceland University. Klaire played collegiate volleyball at Graceland University in Lamoni Iowa as well as coached men's and women's volleyball the past four years.

name: Julie Sweet
description: Whether you're considering downsizing now or in the future, you’ve outgrown your current home, you’re ready for your first home or you’re somewhere in between, I would be happy to help. As a business owner of 15 years, I am resourceful, highly organized and committed to excellent customer service. I have 35 years of marketing, customer service & public relations experience. I am highly detail-oriented, relieving my buyers and sellers of much of the work involved in a typical real estate transaction. I am far more committed to providing exceptional service for a few buyers and sellers at a time than I am in being a "top producer." I truly have a heart for people, am a long-hauler & match pace with my sellers & buyers without pressure.  If you’re looking for a Realtor who will help you think through your options & answer your questions from start to finish, I am

name: Erb Real Estate Group
description: Founded by Team Leader JD Erb, our real estate group is dedicated to providing a high level of customer service and expertise to our clients. ERB Group is a team at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate in Omaha, Nebraska.

name: Staci Mueller
description: Staci Mueller is a passionate and energized REALTOR® for Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate in Omaha, NE. Consistently a Top 10 producing Individual Agent year after year, Staci has been serving the entire metro Omaha area as a full time agent since 2008. She has extensive experience in the acreage and luxury markets, as well as serving buying and selling clients with a gamut of needs from first time home buyers, to retirees, to recreational hunting and lake interests, investment opportunities, and everything in between.

name: Mike Blackmon
description: Mike is the Commercial Division Manager for the Berkshire Hathaway HS | Ambassador Real Estate company, serving the Omaha Metro, Nebraska and Iowa. With a background in sales, banking, and real estate, Mike is 'client-centric', - a 'matchmaker' for his clients and their real estate needs. Includes listing and selling brokerage, landlord AND tenant rep leasing, revitalization and/or re-purposing existing buildings, and new developments. Our Commercial Division has a very strong background and experience in all aspect of new development, construction management, project management, asset management, critical analyis of a building and/or an entire project for analyzing the project feasibility and potential profitability. Mike currently serves as Vice-Chair of the MRCIE (Midlands Regional Commercial Information Exchange) serving Nebraska and Iowa, beginning May1, 2017. Mike is a member of Governmental Affairs Committee for the Omaha Area Board of Realtors. Historically, Mike has been in consultative selling all of his life. Mike invested 12 years in the life insurance and employee benefits business, including financial planning, estate planning, and employee benefit planning, for the medium size business owners and high income earners. Mike earned his professional designation as a CLU in 1976 from The American College in Bryn Mawr, PA, which has proved time and again to be valuable background to assist his real estate clients. An opportunity arose to enter the banking business in a small town bank, where Mike learned all facets of banking, from the teller to the regulatory filings to agriculture, consumer, and commercial business lending. These two careers had a huge impact and fabulous background training for a career in real estate since 1981. Back in Omaha since 2000, Mike has increased his commercial sales, real estate investment analysis skills, and developement and asset management skills with hands-on involvement and counseling a myriad of diffferent experience level of investors and owner/users of commercial real estate. Mike works by referral. If you or your friends and/or associates have a project you are interested in, please feel free to contact Mike to see if we - The Project, Mike - or one of our Team, and You, are a 'Match'!! We love to help make a project come to life and become a success.

name: Kathy Lanphier
description: Kathy has been a licensed real estate agent for more than 20 years now. Many of those years were spent as a Domestic and International Corporate Relocation specialist. As a well-connected professional within the Omaha business community, she has her finger on the pulse of local corporations.

name: Catherine Cizek Klavins
description: Welcome!
